body:
Ever since Taric&#039;s rework, I&#039;ve played him a considerable amount. Also, I had one good game against a Thresh, and decided to see if Taric actually counters Thresh. Whenever I saw the enemy team take Thresh, with me in support and still have my turn to pick, I picked Taric to counter him. I&#039;ve won every game so far with me as Taric against Thresh matchup (probably 4 matches so far).

Here&#039;s why it works:
- if Thresh hooks you, after you&#039;re stunned/knocked up (from Flay), you shield yourself and use your stun (Dazzle). Thresh will take considerable damage, especially if your ADC follows up with some poke, and Taric is usually tanky enough to win that damage trade;
- if Thresh hooks your ADC, use your stun right away if he goes in. Thresh will not have time to use his Flay because he will be stunned, have taken AP damage, and then will be low health;
- from what I&#039;ve observed, Taric is more tanky than Thresh, especially if Thresh gets behind in collecting souls;
- when the enemy jungler comes to gank and you&#039;re squeezed in a tight spot, use your ult and then GTFO;
- OR use your ult to tower dive when your jungler comes to gank.

Other observations on the Taric/Thresh matchup?
